&gt;&gt; Valerie Frey: I don't know.

01:02:41.490 --> 01:02:42.790
I mean there's some times like,
you know, trying to teach somebody

01:02:42.790 --> 01:02:46.200
to love history or teach them
to love their family history.

01:02:46.200 --> 01:02:47.560
It can be a long road.

01:02:47.560 --> 01:02:50.710
But sometimes it can always
again turn on a dime, you know,

01:02:50.710 --> 01:02:54.250
to get them to understand
that the recipes

01:02:54.250 --> 01:02:55.650
that they have are very specific.

01:02:55.650 --> 01:02:59.360
They were chosen -- brought into
the family for various reasons.

01:02:59.360 --> 01:03:01.660 position:56%
And they really reflect that family.

01:03:01.660 --> 01:03:04.180
And it's sort of a
unique conglomeration

01:03:04.180 --> 01:03:07.700
that will never ever come
again, that collection.

01:03:07.700 --> 01:03:09.860
So that's probably the
way I would approach it,

01:03:09.860 --> 01:03:14.170
is even if they're not the most
unique recipes in the world,

01:03:14.170 --> 01:03:16.550
it's a unique collection.

01:03:16.550 --> 01:03:18.020
And I guess we're getting
sort of short on time.

01:03:18.020 --> 01:03:20.090
Let me take one more
question though.

01:03:20.090 --> 01:03:24.190
&gt;&gt; When you did your cookbook,
and there was a relative

01:03:24.190 --> 01:03:31.870
who had not given you a recipe,
do you think sometimes they're --

01:03:31.870 --> 01:03:35.120
well, I'm not going to
give that one recipe.

01:03:35.120 --> 01:03:38.430
You know, that's my recipe.

01:03:38.430 --> 01:03:39.730
&gt;&gt; Valerie Frey: Yeah.

01:03:39.730 --> 01:03:41.440
&gt;&gt; And any suggestions
that you would have --

01:03:41.440 --> 01:03:44.630
I think producing the
cookbook, that's a good thing

01:03:44.630 --> 01:03:46.550
because they under -- they see it.

01:03:46.550 --> 01:03:48.820
But yet that recipe was
contained in it [inaudible].

01:03:48.820 --> 01:03:51.540
You understand what I'm saying.

01:03:51.540 --> 01:03:52.840
&gt;&gt; Valerie Frey: Yes.

01:03:52.840 --> 01:03:54.140
That was a problem I came
across over and over again.

01:03:54.140 --> 01:03:56.300
And I did, I did talk
about it in the book.

01:03:56.300 --> 01:03:59.810
That a lot of times it's
a quality control issue.

01:03:59.810 --> 01:04:03.190
This is my pet recipe and what if
you don't do a good job with it

01:04:03.190 --> 01:04:04.830
and then you say it's mine?

01:04:04.830 --> 01:04:07.860
So a lot of times when I --

01:04:07.860 --> 01:04:10.630
when someone is kind enough to
give me a real signature recipe,

01:04:10.630 --> 01:04:14.050
I assure them that I will
take great pains with it.

01:04:14.050 --> 01:04:16.080
Also a lot of times, people
really want to be credited

01:04:16.080 --> 01:04:18.520
for that something special
that they've developed.

01:04:18.520 --> 01:04:22.050
And so I will tell them, this
will have your name in the title.

01:04:22.050 --> 01:04:25.160
And I will not change
anything about it.

01:04:25.160 --> 01:04:28.160
And sometimes that puts
people's fears to rest.

01:04:28.160 --> 01:04:30.780
But I came across so
many stories about that.

01:04:30.780 --> 01:04:33.820
And what I recommended is
if they just can't stand

01:04:33.820 --> 01:04:37.540
to not have the corner on the
market, have them write it

01:04:37.540 --> 01:04:41.180
down in detail as best they can
and put it with their last will

01:04:41.180 --> 01:04:43.570
and testament [laughter].

01:04:43.570 --> 01:04:45.300
That's the -- sort
of they can have it.

01:04:45.300 --> 01:04:47.640
But one of the things that
I pointed out to them --

01:04:47.640 --> 01:04:51.430
if you hold that recipe
forever and you die with it,

01:04:51.430 --> 01:04:56.140
people will talk longingly about
it for, oh, a decade, maybe two,

01:04:56.140 --> 01:04:58.020
and then you vanish into the ether.

01:04:58.020 --> 01:05:00.800
But if you've saved that
recipe and you've shared it,

01:05:00.800 --> 01:05:04.920
and you've taken pains with it,
you'll become legendary [laughter].

01:05:04.920 --> 01:05:07.230
&gt;&gt; Yeah, thanks.

